# Frontend

## Stack
React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, React Router, lucide-react, General Sans (Fontshare)

## UX rules
- Default post-login screen: **Inbox**, not a KPI vanity dashboard
- Prioritize: upload, document status, anomalies, follow-up actions, readiness
- Structured actions and buttons — not open-ended prompts
- Right-side AI agent workspace allowed but must stay task-oriented
- Premium, dense, professional UI — no purple gradients, startup aesthetics, or generic feature cards

## Routes
`/app/inbox` | `/app/documents/:id` | `/app/readiness` | `/app/followups` | `/app/exports` | `/app/jobs` | `/app/agents`

## Coding
- TypeScript strict — avoid `any`
- Reuse existing components before creating new ones
- Minimal diffs; do not rename files or add packages unless asked
- Never invent backend endpoints without labeling TODO/mock
